  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "To remove a non-friend from your Facebook Messenger contact list, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Messenger:** Launch the Facebook Messenger app on your mobile device or go to the Messenger website on your computer.\n\n2. **Find the Contact:** Scroll through your contact list or use the search function to find the person you want to remove.\n\n3. **Open the Chat:** Tap or click on the chat with that contact to open the conversation.\n\n4. **Access Contact Information:**\n   - On mobile: Tap on the person\u2019s name or the \"i\" icon in the top right corner of the chat to open the contact's information.\n   - On desktop: Click on the name at the top of the chat to access the settings.\n\n5. **Block the Contact (if necessary):** If you want to completely remove them from your experience, you may choose to block them:\n   - At the contact information screen, scroll down and select \"Block.\"\n   - Confirm that you want to block the user.\n\n6. **Hide/Remove from Contacts (if applicable):** While you can't technically \"remove\" non-friends from Messenger, you can hide conversations. To do this, go back to the main Messenger screen, find the chat, swipe left (mobile) or click and hold (desktop) on the conversation, and select \"Delete.\" This removes the conversation from your list but does not block the person.\n\n7. **Adjust Privacy Settings:** You can manage who can send you messages by changing your privacy settings on Facebook. Go to your Facebook account settings, look for the privacy section, and adjust message settings.\n\nRemember that blocking someone on Messenger also blocks them on Facebook. If you don\u2019t want to block the person but just want to remove them from view, you might just hide the conversation without blocking.",
